# Hallucination Checks Implementation Walkthrough

I have implemented a comprehensive hallucination detection system within the governance layer of the contract agent.

## Changes Made

### 1. Base Governance Updates
- Modified [IGuardValidator](file:///c:/AntiGravity-AI/contract_agent_capstone/backend/governance/base.py#18-49) and [BaseGuard](file:///c:/AntiGravity-AI/contract_agent_capstone/backend/governance/base.py#50-110) in [base.py](file:///c:/AntiGravity-AI/contract_agent_capstone/backend/governance/base.py) to support optional `context_metadata`. This allows validators to access source contract text during validation.
- Updated all existing validators (PII, Safety, Topic, etc.) to maintain compatibility with the new interface.

### 2. Hallucination Validator
- Created [hallucination.py](file:///c:/AntiGravity-AI/contract_agent_capstone/backend/governance/validators/hallucination.py):
    - Implements an LLM-based "Critic" pattern.
    - Compares the AI's generated response against the `source_text` provided in the context.
    - Detects unsupported numbers, parties, and legal claims.
    - Returns `is_safe=False` with a detailed reason if a hallucination is detected.

### 3. Output Guard Integration
- Integrated [HallucinationValidator](file:///c:/AntiGravity-AI/contract_agent_capstone/backend/governance/validators/hallucination.py#8-83) into the [OutputGuard](file:///c:/AntiGravity-AI/contract_agent_capstone/backend/governance/output_guard.py#5-36) default chain in [output_guard.py](file:///c:/AntiGravity-AI/contract_agent_capstone/backend/governance/output_guard.py).
- Updated [main.py](file:///c:/AntiGravity-AI/contract_agent_capstone/backend/main.py) to automatically extract `source_text` from all tool execution results (e.g., contract search results) and pass it to the governance layer.
- Ensured consistent use of `gemini-2.5-flash` across all governance components for reliable validation.

## Verification Results

